Pin: GPIO -> 100 ohm gate resistor -> AO3400 gate. 100 k gate-to-GND. Source -> GND. Drain -> solenoid -. Solenoid + -> 12 V. Flyback diode 1N4007 across solenoid (cathode to 12 V).

```cpp
const int SOL_PIN = 7;

void setup() { pinMode(SOL_PIN, OUTPUT); }

void pulse(unsigned long ms) {
  digitalWrite(SOL_PIN, HIGH);
  delay(ms);
  digitalWrite(SOL_PIN, LOW);
}

void loop() {
  pulse(50);          // fire 50 ms
  delay(2000);
}
```

Check duty cycle: 12 V solenoids are typically rated 25 percent ED (energized duration). If you keep it on continuously the coil overheats. For 'always on' applications add a holding circuit: full pulse for 50 ms to pull in, then 30 percent PWM to hold.

DRV8833 channel: AIN1, AIN2 control direction and PWM. Truth table per channel:
- AIN1=PWM, AIN2=0: forward, speed = duty
- AIN1=0,   AIN2=PWM: reverse, speed = duty
- AIN1=1,   AIN2=1: brake (short windings)
- AIN1=0,   AIN2=0: coast (high-Z)

```cpp
const int A1 = 5;
const int A2 = 6;

void setup() {
  pinMode(A1, OUTPUT);
  pinMode(A2, OUTPUT);
}

void drive(int speed) {  // -255..255
  if (speed > 0) {
    analogWrite(A1, speed);
    digitalWrite(A2, LOW);
  } else if (speed < 0) {
    digitalWrite(A1, LOW);
    analogWrite(A2, -speed);
  } else {
    digitalWrite(A1, LOW);
    digitalWrite(A2, LOW);
  }
}
```

DRV8833 max 1.5 A continuous per channel, 2 A peak. For larger motors use TB6612FNG (1.2 A continuous, 3.2 A peak) or BTS7960 (43 A).
